  "number": "6.4",
  "title": "Slope and Rates of Change",
  "body": " Slope and Rates of Change  Linear equations can provide simple models of real-life scenarios. The essential feature of a linear model is a constant rate of change determined by the slope of the line.   Linear Model of Data  Researchers collected data on the number of hours students studied for an important professional certification exam. They performed a common statistical technique called linear regression to establish a best-fit linear model of the data and found the linear relationship where is the number of hours studied and is the predicted score on the exam. For each hour of studying, the model predicts an increased score of points. This rate of change of  points per hour is seen graphically in the steepness or slope of the graph of the line.    Slope of a Line  The slope of a line in the coordinate plane is the ratio of the change in over the change in between any two different points on the line. Precisely, suppose and are two points on a line with . Then   The symbol is commonly used for the slope of a line. The vertical change in is often called the rise and is denoted , where the Greek letter \"delta\" is used to indicate change (difference). Similarly, horizontal change in is often called the run and is denoted .   Finding the Slope   Find the slope of the line between the two points and    Compute rise over run from the given points, being sure to maintain the correct order when subtracting:  The slope is negative, indicating that an increase of units in the -coordinate will result in a decrease of unit in the -coordinate.     Horizontal and Vertical Lines  The graph of a linear equation of the form is a horizontal line and its slope is zero. This is because a change in results in no change in . On the other hand, a linear equation of the form is a vertical line and its slope is undefined . This is because the change in the -coordinates between any two points on the line is zero and we must never divide by zero.   Horizontal and Vertical Lines  The line is horizontal with slope , while the line is vertical with undefined slope.      "
